sensors.sensor_info:
Used to measure the speed and
 height of the tide and other
 weather metrics.
sensors.sensor_ext_info:
A tide gauge is a device used to measure the change in sea level relative to the surface of land.
Sensors continuously record the height of the water level by measuring the distance to the water's surface and comparing it to the height of the land it is connected to.
Tide gauges are important sensors when predicting upcoming storms, since storms create higher waves.
